Ibrahim Maliki (amụrụ ya na Julaị 15, 1981) bụ onye Naijiria bụbu onye na-egwu mmiri, onye ọkachamara na sprint freestyle events

Maliki ruru eru maka 50m freestyle nke ụmụ nwoke na  Summer Olympics nke afọ 2004 na Athens, na-enweghị oge ntinye. Ọ mara ndị ọzọ ise na-egwu mmiri aka na okpomọkụ otu, gụnyere Emile Rony Bakale nke obodo Congo dị afọ iri na isii
O weputara ihe kacha mma nke 26.81 iji nweta ebe nke atọ site na 1.34-second margin n'azụ onye mmeri Bakale
Maliki enweghị ike ịga n'ihu rụọ ọkara ikpeazụ, ebe ọ nọ n'ọnọdụ nke iri isii na itoolu n'ime ndị na-egwu mmiri iri asatọ na isii na mbido egwuregwu ahụ.
